# Legacy Structure Inventory

## Purpose

Use this document to capture the current structure of an existing repository before reshaping its documentation.

## Current Top-Level Structure

- `path/`: what it contains
- `path/`: why it exists

## Existing Document Entry Points

- current `README`
- project-level guidance files
- hidden workflow docs
- external documents still relied on by the team

## Known Gaps

- undocumented directories
- undocumented workflows
- inconsistent terminology
- missing ownership or maintenance rules

## Reshape Priorities

1. add missing repository entry documents
2. document current structure and terms
3. add workflow and delivery documents
4. add versioned feature docs only where useful
